stix:Indicator.indicator:Description:
This file is associated with "Kuluoz.B" malware which is a variant of the "Win32/Winwebsec" malware family. The malware creates a process named "svchost.exe". This process only exists in memory and has no physical file on the hard drive associated with it.

The purpose of "svchost.exe" is to load a DLL file named "dll.dll" embedded within it. The embedded DLL has one exported function "Work". The "dll.dll" file has an array of hard-coded "IP Addresses : Port number" pairs:

